items.sentence: According to Tom, Mary will be here tomorrow.
Tom struggled to keep up with the coursework.
Weren't you supposed to get home before 2:30?
I never get home on Mondays until after 2:30.
No one knows how long the pandemic will last.
Tom ate the cupcakes I was going to give you.
You didn't want to do that with Tom, did you?
You did that the way Tom told you to, I hope.
You did that just to impress Tom, didn't you?
You asked Tom why he'd done that, didn't you?
